metaclass.name: PersonSystem
metaclass.description: A Person is defined by her his name and email.A Person can access HOPEX as soon as the Administrator assigns her him a connection identifier (Login) and a profile.

properties.name: UserCode
properties.description: The User Code is the short identifier (upper case, maximum length 6 characters) of the user that serves as the basis for private workspace naming.Do not modify its MetaAttribute Length value.

properties.name: CommandLine
properties.description: This field lets you limit the products available for this user. For more details see the administrator s manual.

properties.name: ScciUserName
properties.description: Name used to connect the user to the configuration management system.

properties.name: Email
properties.description: E-mail of an Org-Unit, a Person, a MEGA User, etc.

properties.name: BelongsToAPersonGroup
properties.description: define wether the MEGA Person belongs to a group or not.In that case, the MEGA Person will connect to the application with the role defined on the group.

properties.name: ValidPerson
properties.description: Validity of the object  Person :  - Incomplete: the person has a login but does not have an e-mail.  - Invalid: the person does not have a login.   - Valid: the person has a login, an e-mail and at least one profile assigned.

metaclass.name: Login

properties.name: MetaAttributeType
properties.description: This parameter defines the internal type of a MetaAttribute.Possible values: 	String: X. Use it for alphanumeric and numeric values if not used to compute data. Value must belong to [0-1024]  	VarChar: A. ANSI. Use it for large texts like comments 	Datetime: D. Use it for dates 	Boolean: 1. Values are 0 or 1. Not recommended. Use rather String with a tabulated values 	Short: S. Use it for small numbers if you compute data. Value must belong to [0-65535] 	Double: H. Use it for numbers if you compute data. Value must belong to [0-18446744073709551616] 	Long: L. Value must belong to [0-4294967295] 	Float: F. Use it for large numbers if you compute data.  	Binary: Q. Internal. Do not use it 	VarBinary: B. Internal. Do not use itNote: the internal format of date is  YYYY MM DD HH:MM:SS

properties.name: MetaAttributeLength
properties.description: This parameter defines the maximum length of a MetaAttribute.Value must belong to [1-1024]Notes: 	Not considered for the MetaClass name 	Mandatory for  String  Meta Attribute type. Keep null for other types 	Previously called  _AtLength

properties.name: MetaAttributeFormat
properties.description: This parameter defines for a metamodel element (MetaAttribute, TaggedValue) the appropriate control for the MetaAttributePossible values: 	Standard: S (default). Use it for strings. 	Enumeration: F: use it string type with predefined list of values 	Enumeration (Opened): T. Use it for string type with list of values open to user input 	Duration: D. Use it for dates 	Percent: P. Use it to display percentages 	Double: E. Use it to display numbers 	Object: O. Use it to display objects 	Signed Number: Z. Use it to display signed numbers. 	Relative: R. Internal. Do not use it.

properties.name: Abbreviation
properties.description: This parameter defines an alias for a metamodel element (MetaAssociation, MetaAssociationEnd, MetaAttribute, MetaClass, TaggedValue). This alias is a shortname used for display.Possible value : string [0-20] characters.Do not set a value for this property if you are not an expert.

metaclass.name: SystemProcess
metaclass.description: A system process is the executable representation of a process. A System Process is formally described by the workflow Events, the Tasks to be carried out during the processing, the sequence of the Tasks and the information exchanged between the participants. In the BPMN notation, the system process represents a sub-process from the system point of view.

properties.name: Name

properties.description: Beginning of the production period

properties.description: End of the production period

properties.name: OutputLogic
properties.description: Defines output logic: - condition means that following conditions are exclusive - parallelism means that following tasks are executed simultaneously

properties.name: TriggeredByEvent
properties.description: This attribute is used to define that a process is an event sub-process (triggered by event) or not (BPMN 2).

properties.name: Transaction
properties.description: A transaction is a set of coordinated activities leading to a consistent, and verifiable outcome.

properties.name: Loop
properties.description: A loop is a process step that is repeated as long as a condition is true: - Do While: the condition is evaluated before the first execution. - Do Until: the condition is evaluated after the first execution. In this case, the process step is executed at least once.

properties.name: AdHoc
properties.description: Steps of an ad hoc process are not controlled or sequenced in a particular order. Theirperformance is determined by the performers of the process.

properties.name: Multiple
properties.description: The process step is repeated a number of times that is evaluated only once before it is performed. It can be repeated in parallel or sequentially.

enumValues.name: Sequential
enumValues.description: Sequential - Is multiple - SThe process step is repeated sequentially a number of times that is evaluated before it is performed.

enumValues.name: Parallel
enumValues.description: Parallel - Is multiple-YThe process step is repeated  in parallel a number of times that is evaluated before it is performed.

enumValues.name: No
enumValues.description: No - Is multiple-NThe process step is not repeated a number of times that is evaluated before it is performed.

properties.name: Compensation
properties.description: A compensation defines the set of activities that are performed during the roll-back of a transaction to compensate for activities that were performed during the normal flow of the process.

properties.name: LoopCondition
properties.description: The loop execution condition represents the condition which is tested for each iteration to decide if the loop will be executed one more or not.

properties.name: TaskType
properties.description: You can indicate the task type such as process call, send, receive, manual, business rule, script, service (the use of an IT-Service), or user task (with a GUI).

enumValues.name: Manual
enumValues.description: Manual - ManualA Manual task is a task that is expected to be performed without the aid of any business process execution engine or any application. An example of this could be a telephone technician installing a telephone at a customer location.

enumValues.name: Receive
enumValues.description: Receive - ReceiveA Receive task is a simple task that is designed to wait for a message to arrive from an external participant (relative to the process). Once the message has been received, the task is completed.

enumValues.name: Send
enumValues.description: Send - SendA Send task is a simple task that is designed to send a message to an external participant (relative to the process). Once the Message has been sent, the task is completed.

enumValues.name: BusinessRule
enumValues.description: Business Rule - Business RuleA Business Rule task provides a mechanism for the process to provide input to a business rules engine and to get the output of calculations that the business rules engine might provide.

enumValues.name: Script
enumValues.description: Script - ScriptA Script task is executed by a process engine. The modeler or implementer defines a script in a language that the engine can interpret. When the task is ready to start, the engine will execute the script. When the script is completed, the task will also be completed.

enumValues.name: User
enumValues.description: User - UserA User task is a typical workflow task where a human performer performs the task with the assistance of a software application (GUI). It can be scheduled through a task list manager of some sort.

enumValues.name: IT_ServiceCall
enumValues.description: IT-Service Call - IT-Service CallAn IT-Service Call task is a task that uses some sort of service, which could be a web service or an automated application.

enumValues.name: SystemProcessCall
enumValues.description: System Process Call - System Process CallA  System Process Call task is a task that is used to call another process from within the first process.

properties.name: InputLogic
properties.description: Defines input logic: - junction means that processing continues as soon as one of the input messages or triggering sequence flows is available - synchronisation means processing only continues when all input messages or expected sequence flows become available

metaclass.name: OrgUnit
metaclass.description: An org-unit represents a person or a group of persons that intervenes in the enterprise business processes or information system. An org-unit can be internal or external to the enterprise.- An internal org-unit is an organizational element of the enterprise structure such as a department, a service, or a workstation. An internal org-unit is defined based on how detailed you require your view of the enterprise to be (cf org-unit-type). Example: financial management, sales management, marketing department, account manager.- An external entity is an organization that exchanges flows with the enterprise. Example: Customer, Supplier, Government Office.

properties.name: Name
properties.description: Short Name of the object (posibility to get the long name with an argument)

properties.name: InternalExternal
properties.description: The nature of an org-unit indicates whether this org-unit is inside (internal) the enterprise or outside (external).

properties.name: OrgUnitType
properties.description: A  Company  org-unit represent a legal entity such as the company itself, one of its subsidiaries, another partner company, etc.A  Institute  org-unit represents a permanent organizational body created for a usually non-profitable purpose such as education, art, or science.A  Structure  org-unit represents a company department. Example: Sales Department.A  Function  org-unit represents a job title. Example: Sales Representative.A  Manager  org-unit represents the manager of a department. Example: Sales Manager.A  Generic  org-unit represents a role to be played during a procedure. Examples: Writer, Approver, etc.

metaclass.name: Operation
metaclass.description: An operation is an elementary step in an organizational process executed by an org-unit. In BPMN it cannot be broken down.

properties.name: Name
properties.description: Short Name of the object (posibility to get the long name with an argument)

properties.name: OutputLogic
properties.description: Defines output logic: - condition means that following conditions are exclusive - parallelism means that following tasks are executed simultaneously

properties.name: Transaction
properties.description: A transaction is a set of coordinated activities leading to a consistent, and verifiable outcome.

properties.name: Loop
properties.description: A loop is a process step that is repeated as long as a condition is true: - Do While: the condition is evaluated before the first execution. - Do Until: the condition is evaluated after the first execution. In this case, the process step is executed at least once.

properties.name: AdHoc
properties.description: Steps of an ad hoc process are not controlled or sequenced in a particular order. Theirperformance is determined by the performers of the process.

properties.name: Multiple
properties.description: The process step is repeated a number of times that is evaluated only once before it is performed. It can be repeated in parallel or sequentially.

enumValues.name: Sequential
enumValues.description: Sequential - Is multiple - SThe process step is repeated sequentially a number of times that is evaluated before it is performed.

enumValues.name: Parallel
enumValues.description: Parallel - Is multiple-YThe process step is repeated  in parallel a number of times that is evaluated before it is performed.

enumValues.name: No
enumValues.description: No - Is multiple-NThe process step is not repeated a number of times that is evaluated before it is performed.

properties.name: Compensation
properties.description: A compensation defines the set of activities that are performed during the roll-back of a transaction to compensate for activities that were performed during the normal flow of the process.

properties.name: LoopCondition
properties.description: The loop execution condition represents the condition which is tested for each iteration to decide if the loop will be executed one more or not.

properties.name: TaskType
properties.description: You can indicate the task type such as process call, send, receive, manual, business rule, script, service (the use of an IT-Service), or user task (with a GUI).

enumValues.name: Manual
enumValues.description: Manual - ManualA Manual task is a task that is expected to be performed without the aid of any business process execution engine or any application. An example of this could be a telephone technician installing a telephone at a customer location.

enumValues.name: Receive
enumValues.description: Receive - ReceiveA Receive task is a simple task that is designed to wait for a message to arrive from an external participant (relative to the process). Once the message has been received, the task is completed.

enumValues.name: Send
enumValues.description: Send - SendA Send task is a simple task that is designed to send a message to an external participant (relative to the process). Once the Message has been sent, the task is completed.

enumValues.name: BusinessRule
enumValues.description: Business Rule - Business RuleA Business Rule task provides a mechanism for the process to provide input to a business rules engine and to get the output of calculations that the business rules engine might provide.

enumValues.name: Script
enumValues.description: Script - ScriptA Script task is executed by a process engine. The modeler or implementer defines a script in a language that the engine can interpret. When the task is ready to start, the engine will execute the script. When the script is completed, the task will also be completed.

enumValues.name: User
enumValues.description: User - UserA User task is a typical workflow task where a human performer performs the task with the assistance of a software application (GUI). It can be scheduled through a task list manager of some sort.

enumValues.name: IT_ServiceCall
enumValues.description: IT-Service Call - IT-Service CallAn IT-Service Call task is a task that uses some sort of service, which could be a web service or an automated application.

enumValues.name: SystemProcessCall
enumValues.description: System Process Call - System Process CallA  System Process Call task is a task that is used to call another process from within the first process.

properties.name: InputLogic
properties.description: Defines input logic: - junction means that processing continues as soon as one of the input messages or triggering sequence flows is available - synchronisation means processing only continues when all input messages or expected sequence flows become available

metaclass.name: OrganizationalProcess
metaclass.description: An organizational process is a set of operations performed by org-units within a company or organization, to produce a result. It is depicted as a sequence of operations, controlled by events and conditions. In the BPMN notation, the organizational process represents a sub-process from the organizational point of view.

properties.name: Comment
properties.description: This text enables addition of a long description for an object.

properties.name: Id
properties.description: An absolute identifier is a string of characters associated with each object in the repository. This string is computed using the date and time the session was opened, the number of objects created since the session started, and the object creation date (in milliseconds). An absolute identifier provides a unique way to identify an object in the repository, so that even if the object is renamed, all the links to it are retained.

properties.name: Creator
properties.description: absolute identifier of the user who created the object

properties.name: Modifier
properties.description: absolute identifier of the user who last modified the object
